JS_Objects,"Object Functions","Using the brakets notation, create an object named ""seller"" that will have the properties ""first_name"", ""last_name"", ""position"" and ""currentSales"", corresponding to ""John"", ""Doe"",""Staff"" and 5500 respectively.
2.- Then create a declared function ""getData1"" that will return an array of the KEYS of the ""seller"" object. Use as place_holders, vars or parameters the next words, make them suit in the best place: ""myObj"", ""keyValue"", ""propsArray""

3.- Create a variable ""sellerData1"" that will have as value the array returned by ""getData1"" function.

4.- Create a variable ""sellerData2"" that will have as value an array obtained by executing the __________ method on the seller object.

5.- Print them to the console, in one line sellerData1 and sellerData2 on the next line.","var seller = {
